      "rationale": "Mesh refinement study performed on three grid levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells). GCI values ranged from 3.2% to 11.7% across the five operating points; two high-speed conditions exceeded the 5% threshold. Achieved level 1 is below required level 2. Assessment team accepted without remediation, citing schedule constraints."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented and matched to CFD boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data sourced from FDA GCBP benchmark dataset. Fluid temperature during bench testing was not independently recorded; assumed 37°C based on protocol. Hematocrit variability across test samples was ±4%, exceeding the ±2% tolerance specified in the acceptance criteria. Boundary condition fidelity is therefore incomplete. Achieved level 1 falls below required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or NRMSE) reported for hemolysis index across all validation points; systematic bias characterised.",
      "rationale": "Normalised root mean square error of 8.3% computed across 15 experimental data points. Bland-Altman analysis shows no significant proportional bias. Meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) directly correspond to COU decision QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Validation QoIs are the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) and area-weighted mean shear stress, which directly map to the relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion RH < 1 used in the COU. Required level 2 met."
    },
    {
